【Pathological Slide Reiview】

Yi-Hsin Lu

Abstract

This report investigates the impact of high collinearity among variables on the predictability of survival models. Collinearity can lead to unreliable model coefficients. To address this challenge, we employ Principal Component Analysis (PCA), Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator (LASSO), and Akaike Information Criterion (AIC) to identify the optimal variable combination for building robust survival models.

Our analysis reveals that the first three principal components explain approximately 90% variations, with “pT stage” emerging as the most significant component. Furthermore, both LASSO regression and stepwise selection based on AIC consistently select “pT stage,” “PNI”, and “Surgical margin” as the most relevant variables for survival prediction.

Based on these findings, we recommend using “pT stage,” “PNI,” and “Surgical margin” as the core set of variables for constructing survival models, including Overall Survival, Cancer-Specific Survival, and Disease-Free Survival models.

7 Conclusion

  • For the survival model, we utilize PCA, LASSO, and AIC to select the variables. (see Remark)
  • PCA map display the most of variables are lying on the x-axis and y-axis, it means they are from the same direction.
  • Results of LASSO and AIC (see \(\text{Table}\:\text{1}\))
\(\text{Table}\:\text{1.}\)Variables Selection for Models and Methods
Model Method Grade Configuration Invasiveness pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
OS LASSO pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
AIC pT stage PNI Surgical margin
CS LASSO pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
AIC pT stage PNI Surgical margin
DFS LASSO Invasiveness pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin
AIC pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin
BRFS LASSO Grade(0)
AIC Configuration


  • Clearly, Grade is dropped.
  • pT stage, PNI, and Surgical margin are selected from the methods because, except for the “BRFS” model, these variables are effective for the model.
  • In the “BRFS” model, AIC only selects Configuration, and LASSO drops all variables. Even if we add pT stage, LVI, PNI, and Surgical margin into the model, these methods still drop them all.

Remark

  • PCA (Principal Component Analysis), a dimensionality reduction technique, is used to examine the relationships between variables.
  • LASSO (Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator), a regression method, is used for variable/feature selection.
  • AIC (Akaike Information Criterion), a measure of model quality, is used for model selection.
